oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of HQ Co., 329th Inf. Regt., 83rd Div.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Framed panoramic photograph identified at bottom, "Back From France/Headquarters Co., 329th Infantry, A.E.F." The photograph belonged to Isaac Ferrell Dixon, of Defeated, Tennessee. He is pictured kneeling at right, middle row, second in. Dixon initially reported to the 57th Pioneer Inf. Regt., but later transferred to the 329th Inf. Regt., 83rd Div. serving at various times in Co. E or in the Headquarters Company.
